caption: I eat sushi often and this is some of the best BK has to offer. Fresh fish, great quality, and fantastic staff.

Koto Sushi has been a staple in this community for years! I’ve been a huge fan since they had their older smaller location. The customer service and food are 1,000 stars. I highly recommend this family owned and operated business. Value and service cannot be beat.  Best deal is the dinner box and it gives you a chance to try a bunch of delicacies.
Love this place. The maki c combo (the spicy rolls) always hits the spot and the quality is great.

The food was great and the costumer service was excellent I wish I had found this place sooner when you order the food comes out really fast no wait and the whole atmosphere of the place really makes you feel comfortable and everything tasted so fresh

We love eating out. Last night we arrived in this delicious place which friends recommended to us. We enjoyed a delightful experience there with delicious cooking and an efficient team and a talented  cuisine. We put this fine restaurant in our list  and we shall definitely come back very soon. We deeply recommend.

Have ordered from here for years - great sushi, awesome lunch specials, and great value and portion size. Strong recommend for pork katsu dinner box. Friendly service as well. Koto is my go-to for sushi, nothing really comes close in downtown Brooklyn.
Reliably delicious sushi and definitely the best service you’ll get in Brooklyn. Love this place. We can’t wait to go back soon!
Koto is my go-to sushi spot for the last 4 years. They are always reliable, fresh, and fast for delivery. The woman who answers the phone is an absolute sweetheart! Can't ask for much more
Fresh fish and quiet place to relax
Favorite sushi place in the neighborhood. Fish is always SO fresh. Go to delivery spot!!!!
One of my go-to spots to eat. excellent location, clean, and good customer service. Very good job!

I don’t know who that woman is that answers the phone when I’m ordering out for a delivery she is super super super sweet and always remembers me and yet the sushi is so so good so I give this place a five star
Miso Eggplant a must!
I like my tempura without human hairs in it.

Just had a meal at their outdoor seating area and it was fantastic! Everything was freshly made and served quickly, and I was able to enjoy my food under an umbrella while taking in the unwinding of a Sunday afternoon Flatbush. Go Koto! Definitely coming back soon, and again and again after :)
Really good place for sushi in Brooklyn.
Delicious and fresh fish at great prices. Get the sushi for 2! They’re open during the pandemic and are following safety precautions strictly.
I certainly like the food and service, great area next to my residence. The workers are always helpful. I highly recommend this place.

This restaurant is my favorite. I visit a lot of restaurants but to this restaurant I go the most. The team is very attentive and the cuisine they place on your table is so flavorful. I never miss an opportunity to have a decent meal here. Highly recommended.
The lunch specials are big enough to share and always delicious. Never disappointed whether I eat-in or order delivery.
I really enjoyed the food, the service and the prices. Never expected baked onion to be so delicious. Highly recommend!
Great food and friendliest staff. Go for the sushi, stay for the warm smiles.
Good sushi.
Really good sushi, nicely decorated restaurant and friendly staff.
Wow
The Hamachi Kama was amaaazing! Best I've ever had!
Great space, great food, great service!
Love this spot for reliably good food and ambiance. Hours are tricky but worth a try.
Not a big fan of their sushi, but the overall the spot is very nice inside

This place ambience is very romantic,quite and the owners are very warm.Most of all their lunch boxes are all great prices and delicious.I had their teriyaki salmon lunch box very tasty and delicious.I would recommend this place to everyone.
Great sushi with super fresh taste. I had a sushi box to go, and kitchen was pretty fast at making my food. It's not exactly cheap food, but it'd take this place over any premade sushi boxes.
Really enjoy this place every time I visit Barclay center
Best sushi in Brooklyn
Best sushi place in Brooklyn
I loved it.
Great little sushi spot, a hidden treasure

Horrible experience - food delivery took forever. We waited 70 minutes and when i finally called to check on the status the man who answered the phone was incredibly rude. Will never give them my business again.
everything is amazing，good service and good stuff！😁
Beware online delivery. An hour after I ordered, the restaurant called and said I should have received my food and insinuated that I was lying. Didn’t offer a refund or any support. I’m still hungry.
Had a wonderful time eating here today.  Good sushi, good service and reasonably priced.
Love the undon noodle soup with steam shrimp on a cold day !
Good food, reasonably priced with good portions
Delivery experience was excellent, good portions, on time and well made food.
Had excellent Uni here at Koto! A slice of Japan in Brooklyn!
Great place
Good sushi and very warm staff.
Good place to get something to eat

The best sushi in America. Hands down their menu is delicious I have tried almost everything on the menu. Their shrimp tempura roll is amazing. I also like their who udon and Yaki soba. The staff is very friendly and they do not bother you while you were eating. The food was warm and fresh. The place was packed with people and that is a good sign.

Food was good. Was there around 7pm on a Saturday and it was pretty emtpy. Waitress was good about refilling my water glad while we were eating then extremely slow to check in on us when we wanted to order dessert and ended up just getting the check it took so long.
It wasn't half bad. I might come back.
Best sushi I've ever had.
The place was awesome , came regularly to check on us and the food was awesome!

The food is great as well as an exceptional service!  UPDATE: They've moved to a new location just down the corner and things have just gotten even better! Their new place is spacious and beautifully decorated, and the food is still amazing!
I love this place the food is great , and the staff are very friendly.  I'm a two year customer.. love it

The sushi was pretty standard, nothing too special. We had the shrimp mango, yam tempura, Alaska, and spicy tuna rolls. The spicy tuna roll didn't have any spicy sauce on top but was mixed in... it so they say. The Age tofu was decent but the sauce lacked flavour compared to other places.
Outstanding! Stumbled upon this restaurant while in town for Ed Sheeran concert at the Barclay Center. Sushi was excellent. Chefs were great. You won't be disappointed!
Yas!
Good food staff is too serious!!.lol
Discovered a metal staple hidden inside my beef teriyaki from a seamless order. Could have eaten it by mistake—unacceptable.
Still my favorite go to North Brooklyn sushi joint. It is a hidden gem hole in the wall but great food

Small, unassuming, but a great space to dine. I love this place and have been going for many years. The staff is courteous, attentive and kind. They are truly a community restaurant. There is never high traffic, since most of their orders are delivery, which makes it perfect for someone who wants to avoid a crowd. Get a good book, some good sushi and enjoy.
Always good, nice place. Small, usually quiet. Good food and fresh Sushi!

The food is excellent. I had the miso soup and shumai soup. It was fresh and filling. I had the lobster tempura roll with cavier and it was delicious! Everything was fresh with a nice balance of flavors. It is a small place inside but the customer service is very good. The prices are also very reasonable
Great sushi! They delivery is super fast and the presentation shows care during packing and delivery.
Lunch offer is great 12-3pm that comes with 3 rolls just for $10!! Their food quality and taste are great. Definitely visiting again.

Try this japanese restaurant twice because they have the delivery near my apartment! The fish look like old and smell stink! Every time my stomach feel sick after the sushi. We called in for reason but never get respond. So irresponsible establishment! Me and my friend stopped in next time back from visiting the doctor, and try to explain to them. The waitress very friendly listened to our problem then talked to the gentleman in other language . Then she told us sorry about the problem but their sushi is fresh, and gave us a coupon . So shame ! We returned the coupon to the girl. Then the gentleman talked to the waitress with bad attitude in other language. The atmosphere was just so terrible in that moment. We just wanna get out in hole right the way , as we know the gentleman is owner but not welcome about the customer like us. Very irresponsible and rude management. Just feel sorry to the waitress working with us! Never be back again.
I come to Brooklyn for training and always come here for great food.  Love the fact that the price is reasonable and quite amazing.  Tha place is small but still great for a small party.
I absolutely love this place. It's pretty much the only place I ever get my sushi from and I've been a customer for about 7 years.
One of the best lunch specials I've had.
Consistently the best Japanese food I have ever had.

was eating rice and baby bug was crawling in it ,, called them to tell them HORRIBLE costumer service the lady is VERY nasty and told me to order somewhere else ...to have a business that is very competitive .. LEARN HOW TO SPEAK TO COSTUMERS theres ALWAYS somewhere else to go ... its BROOKLYN
❤️ the food, Yakitori Delicious
This restaurant is stunning.
Solid delivery choice. I had the tuna avocado and spicy yellowtail rolls, and the shumai appetizer. All very fresh + tasty. Will definitely order from them again.
Simple and tasty!
I love this place!!!! Food is always fresh and delicious!!!! Best restaurant in the neighborhood. .
Rolls were perfect! The owner was very friendly.
Loved it

I can't say anythign about what the place looked like because I ordered it for delivery.  Even thought they were nice enough to call and confirm my online order, accurate and were very quick about getting it to me.  The rolls I ordered were very skimpy on the fish salmon inside and the rice didn't really taste quite right.
I know delivery sushi might seem like a big no-no, but Koto is my all-time favorite place for just that reason. Yummy sashimi, rolls, dinner specials, and pretty darn quick too.
I regularly get a sashimi dinner here and it is great every time.  Very fresh and well presented.  My wife usually gets beef teriyaki and that is good as well, big portion
